  "instructions": [
    "Cook the farfalle pasta according to package instructions until al dente. Drain.",
    "In a large skillet or wok, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add red onion and garlic; cook for about 2-3 minutes until softened.",
    "Add cherry tomatoes, oregano, smoked paprika, salt, pepper, and nutritional yeast to the skillet with the onions and garlic. Stir well to combine all ingredients.",
    "Stir in cooked pasta and mix thoroughly with the sauce mixture. Cook for an additional 5 minutes on medium-high heat until everything is heated through and combined evenly.",
